@page "/toggle-button"

<RadzenText TextStyle="TextStyle.H2" TagName="TagName.H1" class="rz-pt-8">
    ToggleButton
</RadzenText>
<RadzenText TextStyle="TextStyle.Subtitle1" TagName="TagName.P" class="rz-pb-4">
    Radzen Blazor <strong>ToggleButton</strong> is a button that changes its appearance or color when activated and returns to its original state when deactivated.
</RadzenText>

<RadzenText TextStyle="TextStyle.Subtitle2" TagName="TagName.P" class="rz-pb-4">
    These demos showcase a toggle button with two-way value binding, customizable active state appearance using <code>ToggleShade</code> and <code>ToggleStyle</code>, multiple variants (filled/flat/outlined/text), content options (text/icons/images) with <code>ToggleIcon</code> for state changes, different sizes (ExtraSmall/Small/Medium/Large), and disabled states—perfect for filtering and category selection.
</RadzenText>

